# Promotion Checklist — <name>

**Skill**: <name>
**From**: `staging/<name>/`   **To**: `.claude/skills/<name>/`
**Date prepared**: YYYY-MM-DD

## Pre-promotion verification

- [ ] `eval/check-skill.sh staging/<name>` → **0 FAIL** (WARNs reviewed)
- [ ] `tests.md` has ≥3 real scenarios (golden / edge / error) with a fresh `Last verified:` date
- [ ] Real-work evidence exists (the skill was built from doing the task 2–3×, not from imagination)
- [ ] All sidecars present and referenced from SKILL.md, one level deep (no `a → b → c` chains)
- [ ] Security review done (no secrets; security smells are intentional/explained)
- [ ] Name is lowercase-hyphen, gerund form, matches the folder
- [ ] **Value-add verdict**: PASS | CONCERN | FAIL  (date, lift /50, # seeds) — or **N/A (non-generative)**
      *(generative/judgment skills only — run `eval/value-add-test.md`; a CONCERN/FAIL must be*
      *acknowledged with a fix or written justification, not silently ignored)*

## Promote

```bash
cp -r staging/<name> .claude/skills/
eval/check-skill.sh .claude/skills/<name>   # expect: 0 FAIL
```

## Post-promotion

- [ ] Skill auto-loads in a fresh Claude Code session (repo as cwd)
- [ ] Live-tested with a few real requests
- [ ] (Optional) development-only artifacts archived out of the promoted copy
